## Ingredients
- 2 tbsp oil
- 3 cloves garlic, minced
- 2 tsp garam masala
- 1 tsp salt
- 1 tbsp lemon juice
- 2 tbsp fresh coriander, chopped
- 1 onion, finely chopped
- 1 tbsp grated ginger
- 1 tsp ground cumin
- 1 tsp ground coriander
- ½ tsp turmeric
- 1 tsp chilli powder (to taste)
- 1 can chopped tomatoes
- 2 cans chickpeas, drained and rinsed

## Method
1. Heat the oil in a pan and cook the onion until golden.
2. Add the garlic and ginger, cooking briefly until fragrant.
3. Stir in the garam masala, cumin, coriander, turmeric, and chilli powder for 15 seconds.
4. Add the chopped tomatoes and simmer until thickened.
5. Incorporate the chickpeas and a splash of water, simmering for 10 minutes.
6. Season with salt and stir in the lemon juice.
7. Garnish with fresh coriander before serving.

## Notes
- Adjust chilli powder to suit your heat preference.
- Serve with rice or naan for a more filling meal.
- Leftovers can be stored in an airtight container for up to 3 days.
- This dish can be frozen for up to a month.
